[], "user_mentions": []}, "quoted_tweet": null, "retweeted_tweet": null, "isLimitedReply": false, "communityInfo": null, "article": null}, {"type": "tweet", "id": "2051977925226811702", "url": "https://x.com/UKikaski/status/2051977925226811702", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/UKikaski/status/2051977925226811702", "text": "\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\udde6\u265f\ufe0f \ud835\udded\ud835\uddd8\ud835\udddf\ud835\uddd8\ud835\udde1\ud835\udde6\ud835\uddde\ud835\uddec'\ud835\udde6 \ud835\uddda\ud835\uddd4\ud835\udde0\ud835\uddd5\ud835\udddc\ud835\udde7 | \ud835\udde9\ud835\udddc\ud835\uddd6\ud835\udde7\ud835\udde2\ud835\udde5\ud835\uddec \ud835\uddd7\ud835\uddd4\ud835\uddec \ud835\uddda\ud835\udde5\ud835\uddd4\ud835\udde1\ud835\uddd7\ud835\udde0\ud835\uddd4\ud835\udde6\ud835\udde7\ud835\uddd8\ud835\udde5 \ud835\uddd8\ud835\uddd7\ud835\udddc\ud835\udde7\ud835\udddc\ud835\udde2\ud835\udde1\n\nWhen Putin announced a May 8-9 Victory Day truce, Zelensky already had his next move planned. He announced his own ceasefire first, effective May 5-6, and dared Russia to honor it.\n\nRussia violated it within hours by launching Shahed strikes on Kharkiv, KAB glide bombs on Zaporizhzhia, and a drone group tracked toward Odesa. Ukrainian Defense Ministry advisor Sternenko confirmed it on record: the May 9 truce is void.\n\nThe play was not about the ceasefire. It was about the receipt.\n\nZelensky constructed a trap with two exits, both unfavorable to Moscow: stand down before Victory Day and signal real flexibility towards peace, or attack and forfeit any claim to ceasefire credibility.\n\nRussia chose the latter primarily because complying means recognizing Ukrainian sovereignty and, by extension, Zelensky's constitutional legitimacy.\n\nPutin now arrives at his parade on May 9 having announced a truce he cannot enforce, over a battlefield he cannot quiet, in a war he cannot end. \n\nZelensky handed him a publicly visible defeat and a documented example of Kremlin hypocrisy on the question of ending the war.\n\nWhether that message breaks through the invisible truth barrier in the White House is yet to be seen. Which, quite frankly, is why the Kremlin can, as in this case, act as it pleases. \n\nVideo: Shahed strike in the Kharkiv region earlier today.\n\n#OSINT #Ukraine", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 17, "replyCount": 1, "likeCount": 40, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 2991, "createdAt": "Wed May 06 10:50:35 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 1, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2051977925226811702", "displayTextRange": [0, 234], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "UKikaski", "url": "https://x.com/UKikaski", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/UKikaski", "id": "1197480887430078464", "name": "OSINT Intuit\u2122", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1980381356514254848/ffjt_wSs_normal.jpg", "coverPicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1197480887430078464/1761573819", "description": "", "location": "USA", "followers": 70880, "following": 2548, "status": "", "canDm": true, "canMediaTag": true, "createdAt": "Thu Nov 21 11:44:36 +0000 2019", "entities": {"description": {"urls": []}, "url": {}}, "fastFollowersCount": 0, "favouritesCount": 7948, "hasCustomTimelines": true, "isTranslator": false, "mediaCount": 22365, "statusesCount": 40051, "withheldInCountries": [], "affiliatesHighlightedLabel": {}, "possiblySensitive": false, "pinnedTweetIds": [], "profile_bio": {"description": "Clinical, unsparing, quietly damning OSINT analysis of geopolitical events. Providing timely context before the narrative war begins. NAFO OG 2022.", "entities": {"description": {}}}, "isAutomated": false, "automatedBy": null}, "extendedEntities": {"media": [{"additional_media_info": {"monetizable": false}, "display_url": "pic.twitter.com/fHysfDa4kN", "expanded_url": "https://twitter